OL,3,C'Chronic' under-performance of boys at
OL,4,CGCSE should be treated as major issue
OL,6,FThe "chronic" under-performance of
OL,7,Fboys at GCSE should be treated as a
OL,8,F"major issue", it has been suggested.
OL,10,FThe director of the Centre for
OL,11,FEducation and Employment Research at
OL,12,Fthe University of Buckingham said the
OL,13,Ftalents of boys are not being
OL,14,Fdeveloped as "fully" as they could be,
OL,15,Fwhich could lead to a "decline in the
OL,16,Fnation's economic competitiveness".
