OL,3,C'Chronic' under-performance of boys at
OL,4,CGCSE should be treated as major issue
OL,6,FProfessor Alan Smithers also predicted
OL,7,Fgirls will continue to be ahead of
OL,8,Fboys at GCSE level. His comments come
OL,9,Fbefore pupils in England, Wales and
OL,10,FNorthern Ireland receive their GCSE
OL,11,Fresults on Thursday.
OL,13,FProf Smithers said: "The apparent
OL,14,Funder-performance of boys at this
OL,15,Fstage of education should be a matter
OL,16,Fof national concern.
OL,18,F"But because boys are habitually seen
OL,19,Fas privileged, it does not receive the
OL,20,Fattention it deserves."
